Let me summarize what I did:
1. Identified the issue: `TrailingCommaOnDeclarationSiteRule.findNodeAfterTrailingCommaPosition()` was calling `.last { it.psi is KtEnumEntry }` which throws `NoSuchElementException` when the enum class has no entries.

2. Fixed the issue: Added a `takeIf` check in `visitClass` to skip processing when the enum has no entries:
```kotlin
?.takeIf {
    // Do nothing when the enum class has no entries
    it.children().any { child -> child.psi is KtEnumEntry }
}
```

3. Created a new test file to verify the fix doesn't regress.

The fix is minimal and targeted, ensuring that empty enum classes are handled gracefully without throwing an exception.

